Hér er uppskrifturinn frá https://www.epicurious.com/recipes/food/view/challah-bread-recipe-107945:

Challah Bread Recipe

Ingredients:
• 5 ¼ cups all-purpose flour
• 1 teaspoon kosher salt
• 1 package active dry yeast (2¼ teaspoons)
• 2 cups lukewarm water (90°–100°F)
• 2 tablespoons vegetable oil
• 3 tablespoons honey
• 4 eggs, at room temperature
• Dry yeast, as needed (optional)
• Vegetable oil spray, for coating the bowl and loaf pan (optional)
Steps:
1. Stir together flour, salt, and yeast in a large bowl. Make a well in the center and add warm water. Stir until a dough is formed. Knead the dough until it is elastic and smooth, about 8 minutes by hand or in a stand mixer fitted with the dough hook attachment. Alternatively, you can use an electric mixer fitted with a dough hook to knead the dough for about 10 minutes. You can also use a food processor fitted with the dough blade to knead the dough for about 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic. The dough should be soft but not sticky. If you are using an electric mixer or food processor, scrape down the sides of the bowl or processor once or twice during the kneading process to ensure that all of the ingredients are being incorporated evenly. The dough will have some stickiness when you first knead it, but it will come together into a cohesive ball as you knead it. The dough should be soft but not sticky when you're finished kneading it. If it's too sticky, add more flour by sprinkling it on top of the dough and then folding it into the rest of the dough until it is absorbed. If it's too dry and crumbly, add more water by spooning it on top of the dough and then folding it into the rest of the dough until it is absorbed. Once your Challah bread is fully baked and golden brown on top, remove it from the oven and let it cool on a wire rack for about 15 minutes before slicing and serving!

Hip hop er en kulturel musikgenre og underholdningskultur der udspringer fra USA i det tidlige 1980'er. Det er en blanding af rytmisk musik, tekst, rap og dans. Hip hop opstod i New York og blev hovedsageligt fremført af afroamerikanere i slummene. 

Hip hop blev opfundet af DJ Kool Herc, en DJ fra Jamaica, der blev født i 1955. Herc var den første, der gav sig til at "breakbeat" (bryde beat) med den ene side af en single. Han fik inspireret andre DJ'ere til at gøre samme. Sådan opstod en hel kultur om at danse til den ene side af singlen. Senere fik han opfundet "The Merry-Go-Round", hvor man dansede rundt om et platan træ på gaden og tog ind i nogle hus.

Det første rap skete i slummene i New York, hvor man brugte rappning til at markere sit hold og slå tilbage på andre hold.

Hip hop blev indspillet på pladeselskaberne i USA allerede i 1973. I 1974 blev det første "hip hop album" udgivet af DJ Kool Herc og hans band The Herculoids.

I begyndelsen af 1980'erne begyndte hip hop at brede sig og blev mere og mere populært blandt unge amerikanere. I 1982 blev det første hip hop album udgivet af et internationalt pladeselskab, nemlig "The Message" af Grandmaster Flash and the Furious Five. Siden da er hip hop vokset sig store med mange kendte artister som Tupac Shakur, NWA, Notorious BIG, Eminem, LL Cool J og mange flere.
source: "Hvenær var hip hop fundið upp?"

Ceux-ci sont issus de la culture de la vigne depuis plus de 2 000 ans, puisque les Romains y avaient déjà établi des vignes. Ils ont pour origine la région naturelle des Maures et des Sables, qui fut d'abord un territoire indépendant, puis une partie du royaume de Provence.

Le mourvèdre donne aux vins un goût très particulier caractéristique du terroir. Les vins de Bandol sont réputés pour leur qualité et leur style typique, ce qui en fait des favoris des sommeliers et des amateurs de grands vins. Ils sont aussi très appréciés pour leurs valeurs nutritionnelles et leurs propriétés médicinales. The most common differences between Python and JavaScript are:

1. Object-oriented vs. functional programming
Python is an object-oriented programming language, while JavaScript is a functional programming language. This means that Python emphasizes the creation of objects, classes, and inheritance, while JavaScript emphasizes the creation of functions and their invocation.

2. Type checking and static vs. dynamic typing
Python has a more thorough type checking system than JavaScript, which has a dynamic type system that allows for more flexibility in the code. In Python, variables must be assigned a specific type before use, while in JavaScript, the type of a variable can be determined at runtime.

3. Scope and context management
In Python, variables have a limited scope and are only accessible within the block in which they are defined. In JavaScript, variables can be accessed from anywhere in the code as long as they are not declared as `var` or `let` or used with the `with` statement.

4. Garbage collection vs. manual memory management
Python uses automatic garbage collection to manage memory, while JavaScript requires developers to manually manage memory through techniques such as reference counting and callbacks. This can make it easier to write complex code in Python but more challenging in JavaScript.

5. Standard library vs. third-party libraries
The standard library in Python is extensive and well-documented, while the standard library in JavaScript is smaller and more basic than many third-party libraries available for use in projects. This can make it easier to find libraries for common tasks in Python but more challenging in JavaScript.
